\fs18 \cf4 \cb30 \strokec4 Time flowed on, winters giving way to summers.\cb1 \
\cb30 Her entire world amounted to this tiny stretch of Yunkui Summit, the changing seasons of the mountain were all she would ever see.\cb1 \
\cb30 In endless solitude and ever-present fear, "another self" quietly came into being.\cb1 \
\
\cb30 "...I am a part of her. From beginning to end, we were never apart."\cb1 \
\cb30 "If she is the light, then I am the shadow. If she stands as a lofty idol, then I am the mortal who crawls below."\cb1 \
\cb30 "Unlike her, I have no wish to become some kind of 'hero'..."\cb1 \
